steps.description:
Point up with your right hand, while keeping your left arm on your hip! {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/06/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/06/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Point left, with your whole arm being a 180 degree angle. Obviously you can't point a 180 angle just standing straight; it will not work. To achieve this step, simply turn your torso 45 degrees towards the left and point left. This should make your right shoulder pointing  forward. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/64/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/64/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

From pointing left, move your hand over your face while simultaneously making it a "jazz hand". {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/41/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/41/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Keeping your "jazz hand", only move your elbow to make your arm straight on the right side. This move should look like a semi-circle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3d/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3d/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-6Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Put both of your arms straight up. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/47/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/47/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Bend your arms into you... bring them down. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f9/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f9/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Now put them to your sides, still sticking out. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f5/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f5/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Now to your hips, with your elbows locked! {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3b/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3b/Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Dance-%22Hare-Hare-Yukai%22-Step-7Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
